menu "Development tools"

    config DEV_SCREENSHOT_CONSOLE
        bool "Enable 'screenshot' console command (dev-only, disable for release builds)"
        default n
        select LV_USE_SNAPSHOT
        help
            Registers a 'screenshot' command on the console REPL that
            captures the current LVGL screen (lv_screen_active()) into a
            PSRAM buffer and streams it back over the same serial port as
            base64 text, for use by tools/dev_screenshot.py. Adds ~768 KB
            of transient PSRAM usage per invocation and pulls in the LVGL
            snapshot API.

            Enable this only via 'idf.py menuconfig' in your local
            sdkconfig (sdkconfig is gitignored). Never set this to y in
            sdkconfig.defaults - it must stay off in production/release
            builds.

    config UI_DIAGNOSTICS
        bool "Enable periodic UI memory diagnostics logging (dev-only)"
        default n
        help
            Logs LVGL pool (lv_mem_monitor), internal-RAM, and PSRAM
            free/largest-block/low-watermark figures - each measured
            separately, since MALLOC_CAP_INTERNAL and MALLOC_CAP_SPIRAM
            describe disjoint regions and OR-ing them into one
            heap_caps_get_free_size() call would silently mix the two -
            plus the active Settings view, live Wi-Fi row count, and
            resident Settings-sub-screen count (should never exceed 1).

            Logged at ESP_LOGI every ~30 ticks of the 1s UI update timer,
            on every Settings view transition, and after each Wi-Fi/
            Watchlist list rebuild - ESP_LOGI rather than ESP_LOGD because
            this project's default CONFIG_LOG_MAXIMUM_LEVEL (INFO) compiles
            ESP_LOGD out entirely, which would make this option silently do
            nothing without also raising the global log ceiling. These
            automatic call sites are compiled out entirely when this option
            is off, so periodic logging costs nothing in a normal build -
            the underlying measurement is still reachable on demand via the
            "memlog" console command (CONFIG_DEV_SCREENSHOT_CONSOLE),
            independent of this option.

            Enable this only via 'idf.py menuconfig' in your local
            sdkconfig (sdkconfig is gitignored). Never set this to y in
            sdkconfig.defaults - it must stay off in production/release
            builds.

endmenu
